<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880526-0043 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: American Bankers Insurance Group </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ABIG GE </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   American Bankers Insurance Group Inc. said it agreed in principle to sell a British subsidiary to Allegiance Capital Partners for #39.8 million ($74.4 million).    American Bankers said in Miami that the sale of its Financial Insurance Group Ltd. subsidiary, a marketer of credit insurance in the United Kingdom, is subject to execution of a definitive agreement and various regulatory clearances.    Allegiance Capital Partners is a partnership between Allegiance Capital Corp. and a General Electric Capital Corp. subsidiary. General Electric Capital is a unit of General Electric Co., Fairfield, Conn. </TEXT></DOC>